{{Infobox library |name = Republic Polytechnic Library |image = File:Republic Polytechnic Library south, Singapore.jpg |caption = South side |location = [[Republic Polytechnic]], [[Singapore]] |scope = Education |website = [https://www.rp.edu.sg/library www.rp.edu.sg] }}
The '''Republic Polytechnic Library''' [共和理工学院图书馆] serves the [[Republic Polytechnic]] and is located on the campus in [[Woodlands, Singapore]]. The [[library]] started its operations on June 18, 2003 from a temporary site in Tanglin Road. It relocated to the Woodlands campus site in February 2006. The current library was opened on the April 10, 2006, with {{convert|9400|m2}} of space.
==Design== The library<!-- The entire campus --> was designed jointly by Japanese architect [[Fumihiko Maki]] and DP Architects. The library is situated at the heart of the Agora, a public space for the interaction and the exchange of information and ideas. In support of Republic Polytechnic’s pedagogical approach based on [[problem-based learning]], the library spaces are flexible, adaptable, and less structured so that spontaneous activities can occur throughout.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.designsingapore.org/pda/award-recipients/2009/republic-polytechnic|title=Republic Polytechnic|website=DesignSingapore.org|publisher=Ministry of Communications and information}}</ref>
== History == The library started out in the Tanglin Campus, opening on the June 18, 2003, and was an actively used library for 3 years. It provided {{convert|1300|m2}} of space and was designed by the [[National Library Board]] with an aim of being trendy and inviting to teenagers. During these 3 years between 2003 and 2006, the library hosted more than 30 local music groups in a local music awareness programme created by Bob Tan of the Centre of Culture and Communication. It relocated to the Woodlands campus site in April 2006.<ref name="las">{{Cite web|url=http://www.las.org.sg/wp/bulletin/swanky-new-library-for-republic-polytechnic/|title=Swanky New Library for Republic Polytechnic – Singapore Libraries Bulletin|website=www.las.org.sg|language=en-US|access-date=2018-04-05}}</ref> The current library was opened on the April 10, 2006 with {{convert|9400|m2}} of space. It is currently managed by Cybrarian Ventures Pte Ltd, a wholly owned company of the National Library Board (NLB) of Singapore.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.cvpl.com.sg/home |title=Cybrarian Ventures Pte Ltd|access-date=3 November 2016}}</ref>
