The '''University of Wales Act 1902''' (2 Edw. 7 c. 14) was an [[Act of Parliament]] of the [[Parliament of the United Kingdom]], given the royal assent on 22 July 1902.
It provided that if any office was stipulated as being open to graduates of the universities of [[University of Oxford|Oxford]], [[University of Cambridge|Cambridge]], [[University of London|London]], or the [[Victoria University (UK)|Victoria University]], or any legal exemption was provided to graduates of those universities, then these privileges would likewise extend to the graduates of the [[University of Wales]] holding equivalent degrees.
The Act was repealed by the [[Statute Law (Repeals) Act 1998]]<ref>{{UK-LEG|type=ukpga|path=ukpga/1998/43|title= Statute Law (Repeals) Act 1998}}</ref>
